## Project Overview

Built a production-grade 3-tier network architecture on AWS using VPC Peering to connect three isolated VPCs — Web, App, and DB. Each tier is a separate VPC with its own security boundary. Traffic can only flow in one direction down the chain: Web → App → DB. Direct Web to DB communication is architecturally impossible — not blocked by a firewall rule, but by the absence of a peering connection and route.

**What makes this real-world:**
- True 3-tier isolation — Web, App, DB are completely separate VPCs
- No transitive routing — Web cannot reach DB even through App
- Defense in depth — isolation enforced at BOTH routing AND security group layers
- Least privilege security groups — each tier only accepts traffic from the tier directly above it
- SSH jump host pattern — single entry point into the private network

