## Why VPC Peering vs Transit Gateway

```
  Transit Gateway (Project 1):        VPC Peering (This Project):

  All VPCs connect through one hub     Direct point-to-point connections
  Transitive routing works ✅          Non-transitive ❌ (by design)
  Charges per attachment per hour      Free (only data transfer costs)
  Best for 5+ VPCs                     Best for simple 2-3 VPC setups
  Centralized routing management       Each connection managed separately
```

Use VPC Peering for simple architectures with strict point-to-point isolation.
Use Transit Gateway when you need centralized routing across many VPCs.

