## IP Addressing

| VPC | CIDR | Subnet | Subnet CIDR | Type |
|-----|------|--------|-------------|------|
| web-vpc | 10.0.0.0/16 | web-public-subnet | 10.0.1.0/24 | Public |
| app-vpc | 10.1.0.0/16 | app-private-subnet | 10.1.1.0/24 | Private |
| db-vpc | 10.2.0.0/16 | db-private-subnet | 10.2.1.0/24 | Private |

VPC Peering requires completely non-overlapping CIDRs. AWS rejects peering between overlapping ranges. Each VPC gets its own /16 block — second octet increments per VPC.

