## Connectivity Design

### Peering Connections

| Connection | Requester | Accepter |
|------------|-----------|---------|
| web-app-peer | web-vpc | app-vpc |
| app-db-peer | app-vpc | db-vpc |

### Route Tables

**web-rt:**

| Destination | Target | Why |
|-------------|--------|-----|
| 10.0.0.0/16 | local | Local VPC traffic |
| 0.0.0.0/0 | web-igw | Internet access |
| 10.1.0.0/16 | web-app-peer | Web → App |

No route to 10.2.0.0/16 — no peering connection exists to point it to.

**app-rt:**

| Destination | Target | Why |
|-------------|--------|-----|
| 10.1.0.0/16 | local | Local VPC traffic |
| 10.0.0.0/16 | web-app-peer | App → Web |
| 10.2.0.0/16 | app-db-peer | App → DB |

**db-rt:**

| Destination | Target | Why |
|-------------|--------|-----|
| 10.2.0.0/16 | local | Local VPC traffic |
| 10.1.0.0/16 | app-db-peer | DB → App only |

### Security Groups

**web-sg:**

| Type | Port | Source | Why |
|------|------|--------|-----|
| HTTP | 80 | 0.0.0.0/0 | Public web server |
| SSH | 22 | 0.0.0.0/0 | Jump host access |
| All ICMP | All | 10.1.0.0/16 | App VPC can ping |

**app-sg:**

| Type | Port | Source | Why |
|------|------|--------|-----|
| SSH | 22 | 10.0.0.0/16 | Web VPC only |
| All ICMP | All | 10.0.0.0/16 | Web VPC only |

**db-sg:**

| Type | Port | Source | Why |
|------|------|--------|-----|
| SSH | 22 | 10.1.0.0/16 | App VPC only |
| All ICMP | All | 10.1.0.0/16 | App VPC only |

### Defense in Depth

```
  Web → DB blocked at TWO independent layers:

  Layer 1 — Routing:        No route in web-rt for 10.2.0.0/16
  Layer 2 — Security Group: db-sg only allows traffic from 10.1.0.0/16

  Both layers must fail for DB to be reachable from Web.
```

